Program: Outlook
Title: 24/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gq5vp
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 25 May 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, claims of torture and abuse from an Egyptian teacher who spent time in a military prison during the uprising. Also the reluctant sangoma - a young South African who's torn between modern life and her family's traditional beliefs. And artist Lisa Gunn, who uses her body as inspiration after an accident confined her to a wheelchair. Show less